ity of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogoff records user logoffs.  If this is an interactive logoff, it is recorded on the local system.  If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52996","V-26540","CCI-000067","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"6959","uuid":"7dd6b3bb-7401-41a1-b87d-dd95cfe32bca","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ECF8029CBE8088549A80A7FF335243F18FE49B58\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logoff successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226100","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226100","title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226100","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","rule_id_src":"SV-226100r794280_rule","rule_id":"SV-226100","rule_version":"WN12-AU-000047","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Logon successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration -> System Audit Policies -> Logon/Logoff -> \"Audit Logon\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (V-14230) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nU