R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 00EB83F40C9AA6FAEED07485631AB96E344262AA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Update must be prevented from searching for point and print drivers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226149","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226149","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226149","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226149r852092_rule","rule_id":"SV-226149","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000018","rule_title":"Optional component installation and component repair must be prevented from using Windows Update.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> \"Specify settings for optional component installation and component repair\" to \"Enabled\" and with \"Never attempt to download payload from Windows Update\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Servicing\\\n\nValue Name: UseWindowsUpdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially provide sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Optional component installation or repair must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legac