"id":"V-226156","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226156","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226156r852094_rule","rule_id":"SV-226156","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000025","rule_title":"Device driver updates must only search managed servers, not Windows Update.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Device Installation -> \"Specify the search server for device driver updates\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Search Managed Server\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name: DriverServerSelection\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially provide sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Device driver updates must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51607","V-36678","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8256","uuid":"ad70bd5d-579e-4845-80f9-acf925b4f550","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DC7F6B2E1B9016D0E5D3B72DDBC5933FE2BF47DA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Device driver updates must only search managed servers, not Windows Update.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226157","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226157","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226157","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226157r852095_rule","rule_id":"SV-226157","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000026","rule_title":"Users must not be prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Driver Installation -> \"Turn off Windows Update device driver search prompt\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DriverSearching\\\n\nValue Name: DontPromptForWindowsUpdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents users from being prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53115","V-15703","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"4829","uuid":"53d1577c-5bce-4100-ba4b-29b0aeb1c325","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0BE82BACD630012D5E93F8178E96063EB2D264B3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must not be prompted to search Windows Update for device drivers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226158","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226158","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226158","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226158r794497_rule","rule_id":"SV-226158","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000027","rule_title":"Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must be enabled and configured to only Good and Unknown.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Early Launch Antimalware -> \"Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Good and Unknown\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to some protection mechanisms that load after initialization.  The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application.  At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51608","V-36679","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9572","uuid":"34500da7-82a1-46f9-b334-a1b011a16552","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1F2108537BB31FED004779F247756513BA051A38\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must be enabled and configured to only Good and Unknown.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226159","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226159","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226159","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226159r794498_rule","rule_id":"SV-226159","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000028","rule_title":"Group Policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy -> \"Configure registry policy processing\" to \"Enabled\" and select the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures that the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed.  This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52933","V-4448","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1691","uuid":"42e9eaea-713a-475c-a140-f03210c057bc","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226160","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226160","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226160","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226160r794499_rule","rule_id":"SV-226160","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000029","rule_title":"Group Policies must be refreshed in the background if the user is logged on.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Group Policy -> \"Turn off background refresh of Group Policy\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the registry.\nIf the following registry value does not exist, this is not a finding (this is the expected result from configuring the policy as outlined in the Fix section.):\nIf the following registry value exists but is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\system\\\n\nValue Name: DisableBkGndGroupPolicy\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If this setting is enabled, then Group Policy settings are not refreshed while a user is currently logged on.  This could lead to instances when a user does not have the latest changes to a policy applied and is therefore operating in an insecure context.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52906","V-3469","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7568","uuid":"9b0aaf4c-d77d-401c-b80e-7d660060d07b","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DD41416480493C7DA9BF56C04F5BC73812D46B9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Group Policies must be refreshed in the background if the user is logged on.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226161","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226161","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226161","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226161r794423_rule","rule_id":"SV-226161","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000030","rule_title":"Access to the Windows Store must be turned off.","fix_text":"If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory exists, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> \"Turn off access to the Store\" to \"Enabled\".   \n\nAlternately, uninstall the \"Desktop Experience\" feature from Windows 2012.  This is located under \"User Interfaces and Infrastructure\" in the \"Add Roles and Features Wizard\".  The \\Windows\\WinStore directory may need to be manually deleted after this.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default. If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoUseStoreOpenWith\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and allow access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  Turning off access to the Windows Store will limit access to publicly available applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51609","V-36680","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9268","uuid":"a1b009e8-2ebe-4080-8673-e039cbc573fe","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5D1DD75656722B984FDA4060380F6324C6A647AB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Access to the Windows Store must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226162","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226162","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226162","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226162r794424_rule","rule_id":"SV-226162","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000032","rule_title":"Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52998","V-14260","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4458","uuid":"4856da6a-8855-44e2-aae7-6ecaa8ceb7a4","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A12506F633ACDB2B90BB43EE30C3FCCA24A76C8E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be prevented.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226163","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226163","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226163","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226163r794425_rule","rule_id":"SV-226163","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000033","rule_title":"Event Viewer Events.asp links must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off Event Viewer \"Events.asp\" links\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\EventViewer\\\n\nValue Name: MicrosoftEventVwrDisableLinks\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Viewing events is a function of administrators, who must not access the internet with privileged accounts.  This setting will disable  Events.asp hyperlinks in Event Viewer to prevent links to the internet from within events.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53017","V-15672","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4862","uuid":"2b1e0005-0df2-4c1b-bda1-80ada872cef1","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 36A9E31430F3F49DA21A707DDB10B95DC0957D58\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Event Viewer Events.asp links must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226164","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226164","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226164","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226164r794426_rule","rule_id":"SV-226164","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000035","rule_title":"Errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs must not be reported to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off handwriting recognition error reporting\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\HandwritingErrorReports\\\n\nValue Name: PreventHandwritingErrorReports\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs from being reported to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15704","SV-53116","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3833","uuid":"9b2b97c0-cbb8-494b-9860-6aea1c171a0c","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B90DECE8F20E2D9351647E2A22F2474F494248FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Errors in handwriting recognition on tablet PCs must not be reported to Microsoft.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226165","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226165","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226165","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226165r794427_rule","rule_id":"SV-226165","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000038","rule_title":"The Internet File Association service must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off Internet File Association service\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoInternetOpenWith\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents unhandled file associations from using the Microsoft Web service to find an application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-15674","SV-53021","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9865","uuid":"98bd7dad-61d6-4bcd-a234-6ae4c37b1c9a","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B450BE90C67A552401E82646E044263F746974FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Internet File Association service must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226166","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226166","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226166","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226166r794428_rule","rule_id":"SV-226166","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000039","rule_title":"Printing over HTTP must be prevented.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication settings -> \"Turn off printing over HTTP\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-14259","SV-52997","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1190","uuid":"4accc350-45a2-48e5-b710-2823f1b8eefd","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C94E2E521F206DA0DE774C701E66CCF1A5D93F2F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Printing over HTTP must be prevented.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226167","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226167","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226167","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226167r794429_rule","rule_id":"SV-226167","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000045","rule_title":"The Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \"Turn off Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\SQMClient\\Windows\\\n\nValue Name: CEIPEnable\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting ensures the Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program is disabled so information is not passed to the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-16020","SV-53143","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5294","uuid":"7a9e8ca0-0f3e-4bde-869c-e7bacb1fe76e","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F6487F2977B8167385C6E3FFDF86B55701A4CCB\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Windows Customer Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226168","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226168","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226168","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226168r852096_rule","rule_id":"SV-226168","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000047","rule_title":"Windows must be prevented from using Windows Update to search for drivers.","fix_text"