,"stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7399DBE55F0B036EA9A8079ADAC64474C327FC00\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Setup event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226193","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226193","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226193","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-226193r877391_rule","rule_id":"SV-226193","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000087","rule_title":"The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> \"Specify the maximum log file size (KB)\" to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52963","V-26582","CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"7470","uuid":"a7f7d3d5-c23a-45f2-bc47-fc2f5d6c008e","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D2E57D1748DEC0F4E68ED5258688AB728514404D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226194","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226194","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226194","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226194r794440_rule","rule_id":"SV-226194","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000088","rule_title":"Windows SmartScreen must be enabled on Windows 2012/2012 R2.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Configure Windows SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\" with either \"Give user a warning before running downloaded unknown software\" or \"Require approval from an administrator before running downloaded unknown software\" selected.   \n\nMicrosoft has changed this setting several times in the Windows 10 administrative templates, which will affect group policies in a domain if later templates are used.\n\nv1607 of Windows 10 and Windows Server 2016 changed the setting to only Enabled or Disabled without additional selections.  Enabled is effectively \"Give user a warning\u2026\".\n\nv1703 of Windows 10 or later administrative templates changed the policy name to \"Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen\", and the selectable options are \"Warn\" and \"Warn and prevent bypass\". When either of these are applied to a Windows 2012/2012 R2 system, it will configure the registry equivalent of \"Give user a warning\u2026\").","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems; for other systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Give user a warning\u2026)\nOr 0x00000002 (2) (Require approval\u2026)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the Internet that may be malicious. Warning a user before running downloaded unknown software, at minimum, will help prevent potentially malicious programs from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51747","V-36707","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9941","uuid":"bd3ddb4f-aef5-4bce-ab8a-3a536c0234e7","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DF1C324BA273DBE09CCF360CA179E832C1DED98C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows SmartScreen must be enabled on Windows 2012/2012 R2.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226195","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226195","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226195","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-226195r852107_rule","rule_id":"SV-226195","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000089","rule_title":"Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention (DEP) provides additional protection by performing  checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running.  This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53125","V-21980","CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"7612","uuid":"45cc405b-9305-40ba-83ad-49c44fd22c5b","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4F0EC034A49C1F8D60DECCC86BFCB5E871A130F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226196","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226196","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226196","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-226196r852108_rule","rule_id":"SV-226196","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000090","rule_title":"Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt.  Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53137","V-15718","CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"8888","uuid":"ecb387d4-3fb1-453f-91a5-49faefc8e9fc","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9F50225FAE2D916137368C7CC550DBE038C4464A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226197","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226197","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226197","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226197r794501_rule","rule_id":"SV-226197","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000091","rule_title":"File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> File Explorer -> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will  limit the set of folders applications can open when run in protected mode.  Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53045","V-15683","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3598","uuid":"d41c7ac3-75eb-4004-91a7-cc46d87ad1dc","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5C263FC37EE3C90CFFBECB9139FBD05B2E3D8407\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226198","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226198","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226198","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226198r794441_rule","rule_id":"SV-226198","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000095","rule_title":"The location feature must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Location and Sensors -> \"Turn off location\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nIf location services are approved by the organization for a device, this must be documented.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LocationAndSensors\\\n\nValue Name: DisableLocation\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1 (Enabled)\n\nIf location services are approved for the system by the organization, this may be set to \"Disabled\" (0).  This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The location service on systems may allow sensitive data to be used by applications on the system.  This should be turned off unless explicitly allowed for approved systems/applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51748","V-36708","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9819","uuid":"14439bee-45fa-4d9a-bb41-54d46efbfed7","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a