ervices sessions in both directions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-3454","SV-52899","CCI-000068","CCI-002890"],"reference_identifier":"4882","uuid":"b1e27f45-f068-4ceb-be31-b34ceb275e55","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9C343506AFEE1AB7B7CE3C2576D2D3D9786D66E4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to the required level.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226203","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226203","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226203","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226203r794502_rule","rule_id":"SV-226203","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000103","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must delete temporary folders when a session is terminated.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders -> \"Do not delete temp folder upon exit\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DeleteTempDirsOnExit\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote desktop session temporary folders must always be deleted after a session is over to prevent hard disk clutter and potential leakage of information.  This setting controls the deletion of the temporary folders when the session is terminated.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52901","V-3456","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6288","uuid":"b349fbc5-beb3-4abb-bde7-faa43f61c7c5","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E877BEAA960A370FDA05723A55BAAF2CF591AC0F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must delete temporary folders when a session is terminated.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226204","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226204","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226204","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226204r794503_rule","rule_id":"SV-226204","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000104","rule_title":"Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Temporary Folders -> \"Do not use temporary folders per session\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: PerSessionTempDir\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If a communal temporary folder is used for remote desktop sessions, it might be possible for users to access other users' temporary folders.  If this setting is enabled, only one temporary folder is used for all remote desktop sessions.  Per session temporary folders must be established.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52900","V-3455","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7612","uuid":"87203e70-8f80-4f44-8e63-7c580ae85d70","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 694A6E9262EFED34C15190CD7BBFA3F23CA78B00\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Remote Desktop Services must be configured to use session-specific temporary folders.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226205","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226205","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226205","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226205r794504_rule","rule_id":"SV-226205","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000105","rule_title":"Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> RSS Feeds -> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure.  This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53040","V-15682","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9244","uuid":"eb2e0a45-4bbd-43e9-962e-43b33ca5adcc","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 524B37F73CF44D1588B9521F28DAC6E2B929BFFE\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Attachments must be prevented from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226206","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226206","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226206","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226206r794442_rule","rule_id":"SV-226206","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000106","rule_title":"Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> RSS Feeds -> \"Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain text passwords that could be used to compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51749","V-36709","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4670","uuid":"cfeb6224-57e2-4a5a-b0fb-0e17e3856cd9","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4D3C40B43187A44B271AB3136BA4E66F3675A262\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226207","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226207","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226207","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226207r794443_rule","rule_id":"SV-226207","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000109","rule_title":"Automatic download of updates from the Windows Store must be turned off.","fix_text":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nWindows 2012 R2:\nWindows 2012 R2 split the original policy that configures this setting into two separate ones.  Configuring either one to \"Enabled\" will update the registry value as identified in the Check section.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \n\"Turn off Automatic Download of updates on Win8 machines\" or \"Turn off Automatic Download and install of updates\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nWindows 2012:\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \"Turn off Automatic Download of updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nWindows 2012 R2:\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\\n\nValue Name:  AutoDownload\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)\n\nWindows 2012:\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\WindowsUpdate\\\n\nValue Name:  AutoDownload\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  Obtaining update components from an outside source may also potentially allow sensitive information outside of the enterprise.  Application updates must be obtained from an internal source.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36710","SV-51750","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1011","uuid":"67fb43c2-8b43-409a-8cea-2b3b57424223","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DBEC929E3AF91A53483A905FAAF4B03B42A9200D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Automatic download of updates from the Windows Store must be turned off.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226208","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226208","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226208","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226208r794444_rule","rule_id":"SV-226208","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000110","rule_title":"The Windows Store application must be turned off.","fix_text":"The Windows Store is not installed by default.  If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Store -> \"Turn off the Store application\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The Windows Store is not installed by default. If the \\Windows\\WinStore directory does not exist, this is NA.\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsStore\\\n\nValue Name:  RemoveWindowsStore\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled installation of applications can introduce various issues, including system instability, and provide access to sensitive information.  Installation of applications must be controlled by the enterprise.  Turning off access to the Windows Store will limit access to publicly available applications.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51751","V-36711","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7838","uuid":"5eaa7bb7-6d5e-4393-914c-e60512f48475","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FFBC94A1D46E2B3CCAC67D261393848A15A64696\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Store application must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226209","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226209","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226209","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226209r852112_rule","rule_id":"SV-226209","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000115","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Allow user control over installs\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators.  This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53061","V-15685","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"1827","uuid":"e9050f25-ca13-4c73-9ff1-01584665de01","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 816058E19A562087B081BAD0D65767A24D4AFF76\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from changing installation options.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226210","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226210","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226210","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226210r852113_rule","rule_id":"SV-226210","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000116","rule_title":"The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Always install with elevated privileges\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges.  Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52954","V-34974","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"6137","uuid":"9d440857-ef1a-4205-8038-7d8b46b2a931","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E031E8FE2BC097E61C31465DF869131512FF7490\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226211","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226211","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226211","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226211r794505_rule","rule_id":"SV-226211","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000117","rule_title":"Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Users must be aware of attempted program installations.  This setting ensures users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53056","V-15684","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5865","uuid":"4656805a-ebe4-4c31-8a40-0fd1f88322ee","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 090C5D08873811AF59E82FC23AD62FC663597D21\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226212","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226212","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226212","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226212r852114_rule","rule_id":"SV-226212","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000118","rule_title":"Nonadministrators must be prevented from applying vendor-signed updates.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Installer -> \"Prohibit non-administrators from applying vendor signed updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: DisableLUAPatching\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  This setting will prevent users from applying vendor-signed updates (though they may be from a trusted source).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53065","V-15686","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"3340","uuid":"9173dcf5-7bae-4f6f-8821-3b9ea6c39c97","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7A2D67D999C3CCFE456398F92573526C725F0CBC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Nonadministrators must be prevented from applying vendor-signed updates.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226213","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226213","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226213","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226213r794445_rule","rule_id":"SV-226213","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000120","rule_title":"Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) must be prevented from accessing the Internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Digital Rights Management -> \"Prevent Windows Media DRM Internet Access\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WMDRM\\\n\nValue Name: DisableOnline\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis check verifies that Windows Media DRM will be prevented from accessing the Internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53139","V-15722","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3799","uuid":"40c2a38d-81d0-4b82-907b-14298982b838","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 43DDEAAE3071D68C5804C7017AF94C4A881EA6B2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Media Digital Rights Management (DRM) must be prevented from accessing the Internet.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226214","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226214","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226214","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226214r794506_rule","rule_id":"SV-226214","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000121","rule_title":"Users must not be presented with Privacy and Installation options on first use of Windows Media Player.","fix_text":"If Windows Media Player is installed, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> \"Do Not Show First Use Dialog Boxes\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows Media Player is not installed by default.  If it is not installed, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: GroupPrivacyAcceptance\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting prevents users from being presented with Privacy and Installation options on first use of Windows Media Player, which could enable some communication with the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53069","V-15687","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8868","uuid":"1cd89f30-40ed-48aa-bb0b-61e3f224c075","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226215","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226215","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226215","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226215r852115_rule","rule_id":"SV-226215","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000122","rule_title":"Windows Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic checking for updates.","fix_text":"If Windows Media Player is installed, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> \"Prevent Automatic Updates\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Windows Media Player is not installed by default.  If it is not installed, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutoupdate\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Uncontrolled system updates can introduce issues to a system.  The automatic check for updates performed by Windows Media Player must be disabled to ensure a constant platform and to prevent the introduction of unknown\\untested software on the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53130","V-3480","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"7638","uuid":"4349d40e-eed2-446a-a6f6-f6b38fcd4ec3","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FA97B7EEB7B345D3FB4312970F011A0640FBDBB8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic checking for updates.' was not present o