er."},{"group_id_src":"V-226221","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226221","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226221","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-226221r852118_rule","rule_id":"SV-226221","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000128","rule_title":"The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) -> WinRM Service -> \"Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access.  Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51757","V-36720","CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1793","uuid":"257642fa-a2bf-4703-92e1-2c0cc2175c76","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2E7856C2608226F98B04A99EFA8CBE385E614D01\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226222","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226222","title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226222","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","rule_id_src":"SV-226222r877394_rule","rule_id":"SV-226222","rule_version":"WN12-CC-000130","rule_title":"The Remote Desktop Session Host must require secure RPC communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Remote Desktop Services -> Remote Desktop Session Host -> Security -> \"Require secure RPC communication\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man-in-the-middle attacks and data disclosure attacks.  A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged.  Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52932","V-4447","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"5426","uuid":"65