(e.g., network management products) require the following and must be documented with the ISSO:\n \n-The logon session does not have administrator rights. \n-The display station (e.g., keyboard, monitor, etc.) is located in a controlled access area.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended.  Enabling a password-protected screen saver to engage after a specified period of time helps protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-36656","SV-51758","CCI-000060"],"reference_identifier":"9580","uuid":"5a71afa8-9e83-482f-b37a-bf5afe260bec","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F2766789A88407942256E4F9648FE9596D71209A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'A screen saver must be enabled on the system.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226360","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226360","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226360","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","rule_id_src":"SV-226360r794619_rule","rule_id":"SV-226360","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000003","rule_title":"The screen saver must be password protected.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Control Panel -> Personalization -> \"Password protect the screen saver\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Control Panel\\Desktop\\\n\nValue Name: ScreenSaverIsSecure\n\nType: REG_SZ\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended.  Enabling a password-protected screen saver to engage after a specified period of time helps protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51760","V-36657","CCI-000056"],"reference_identifier":"2760","uuid":"64c1c8db-eb2b-4b0f-8718-ccc56d35201e","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9EF54410BF1EDA365DC44C5DE58FC6B631E73224\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The screen saver must be password protected.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226361","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226361","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226361","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226361r794636_rule","rule_id":"SV-226361","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000005","rule_title":"Notifications from Windows Push Network Service must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Start Menu and Taskbar -> Notifications -> \"Turn off notifications network usage\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoCloudApplicationNotification\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Push Notification Service (WNS) allows third-party vendors to send updates for toasts, tiles, and badges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51762","V-36776","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4700","uuid":"f7711297-bd7a-4095-880c-5f1b87ad7aa7","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0C18EFB82588D19AEF2D2637E848E1E6CD2FE8C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Notifications from Windows Push Network Service must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226362","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226362","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226362","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226362r794637_rule","rule_id":"SV-226362","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000006","rule_title":"Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Start Menu and Taskbar -> Notifications -> \"Turn off toast notifications on the lock screen\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PushNotifications\\\n\nValue Name: NoToastApplicationNotificationOnLockScreen\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Toast notifications that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel.  Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51763","V-36777","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9000","uuid":"4bd64061-d44c-45f8-969e-1446f8a17726","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 381538D286355A77DCB93305E7E27EA2280D05ED\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Toast notifications to the lock screen must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226363","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226363","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226363","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226363r794638_rule","rule_id":"SV-226363","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000007","rule_title":"The Windows Help Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \"Turn off Help Experience Improvement Program\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\\\n\nValue Name: NoImplicitFeedback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting ensures the Windows Help Experience Improvement Program is disabled to prevent information from being passed to the vendor.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53144","V-16021","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8313","uuid":"ef0d7560-9cff-471d-9d2a-86fc44270728","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C7D888C40B5F28D3D5F1711C7AC5E9E649FF3898\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Windows Help Experience Improvement Program must be disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226364","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226364","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226364","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-226364r794639_rule","rule_id":"SV-226364","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000008","rule_title":"Windows Help Ratings feedback must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> System -> Internet Communication Management -> Internet Communication Settings -> \"Turn off Help Ratings\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Assistance\\Client\\1.0\\\n\nValue Name: NoExplicitFeedback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature.  Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and uncontrolled updates to the system.  \nThis setting ensures users cannot provide ratings feedback to Microsoft for Help content.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53145","V-16048","CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7687","uuid":"d4a74998-fc36-4526-9737-a8f5cdfe03f5","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EDF2A5D0F664232A3D672015E3B57DB6936042EC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Help Ratings feedback must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226365","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226365","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226365","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226365r794685_rule","rule_id":"SV-226365","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000009","rule_title":"Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53002","V-14268","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5312","uuid":"1d9ed058-8863-433d-8b4c-9c90bff6f71c","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A957A8B57A540563088D9252204AC4F72B9D6C85\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226366","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226366","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226366","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226366r794686_rule","rule_id":"SV-226366","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000010","rule_title":"Mechanisms for removing zone information from file attachments must be hidden.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Hide mechanisms to remove zone information\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: HideZoneInfoOnProperties\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.  This setting prevents users from manually removing zone information from saved file attachments.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53004","V-14269","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4432","uuid":"f875918e-2f85-4ec0-bebf-675e283117ae","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 627B7EE65E2DBC58D398C613463947F95C96F264\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Mechanisms for removing zone information from file attachments must be hidden.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226367","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226367","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226367","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-226367r794687_rule","rule_id":"SV-226367","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000011","rule_title":"The system must notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Attachment Manager -> \"Notify antivirus programs when opening attachments\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: ScanWithAntiVirus\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attaching malicious files is a known avenue of attack.  This setting configures the system to notify antivirus programs when a user opens a file attachment.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53006","V-14270","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8902","uuid":"008d60fd-f650-4aaf-a7ee-e3c3c4c24ec2","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2D499156A47873AD9E0947F239EEF08797536B8C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The system must notify antivirus when file attachments are opened.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226368","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226368","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00228","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226368","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00228","rule_id_src":"SV-226368r794688_rule","rule_id":"SV-226368","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000012","rule_title":"Users must be prevented from sharing files in their profiles.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Network Sharing -> \"Prevent users from sharing files within their profile\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoInPlaceSharing\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing users to share files in their profiles may provide unauthorized access or result in the exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53140","V-15727","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7561","uuid":"f83bfcca-6473-4401-af4a-bcd36091726a","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D251C013D21FFF3599F5C25CA49463AEC9287B86\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Users must be prevented from sharing files in their profiles.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226369","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226369","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226369","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-226369r852155_rule","rule_id":"SV-226369","rule_version":"WN12-UC-000013","rule_title":"Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic Codec downloads.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for User Configuration -> Administrative Templates -> Windows Components -> Windows Media Player -> Playback -> \"Prevent Codec Download\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding: \n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\WindowsMediaPlayer\\\n\nValue Name: PreventCodecDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows Media Player uses software components, referred to as Codecs, to play back media files.  By default, when an unknown file type is opened with the Media Player, it will search the Internet for the appropriate Codec and automatically download it.  To ensure platform consistency and to protect against new vulnerabilities associated with media types, all Codecs must be installed by the System Administrator.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52921","V-3481","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"8697","uuid":"1eeca3f5-16d9-4222-8f34-ceb4025551e4","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 72E0A72A14E53FF7448512D9C4D11644DF501673\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Media Player must be configured to prevent automatic Codec downloads.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226370","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226370","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226370","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226370r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226370","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000001","rule_title":"The Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53120","V-26469","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2818","uuid":"08fd50bf-dd51-478b-a9cc-e7ae5400c010","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226371","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226371","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226371","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226371r794624_rule","rule_id":"SV-226371","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000002-DC","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Access this computer from the network user right on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Access this computer from the network\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nAuthenticated Users\nEnterprise Domain Controllers\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: If an application requires this user right, this can be downgraded to not a finding if the following conditions are met:\n- Vendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n- The requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n- The application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (V-36661) and required changes frequency (V-36662).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nAuthenticated Users\nEnterprise Domain Controllers","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" right may access resources on the system and should be limited to those requiring it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26470","SV-51142","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6587","uuid":"16dd1889-25ed-4b52-9ae2-1ae0489b4212","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226372","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226372","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226372r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226372","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000003","rule_title":"The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Act as part of the operating system\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that user is authorized to access.  Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52108","V-1102","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9897","uuid":"157ceb07-4fee-49cc-bd9b-07ecc1cb1785","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B00BC4DE57850AC6B9D94460623BDC301EC6FEE8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226373","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226373","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226373r794625_rule","rule_id":"SV-226373","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000005","rule_title":"The Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Allow log on locally\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52110","V-26472","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5182","uuid":"a1149596-ffa1-4b0e-82cb-78f83b09c40c","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 532685CF150E9F64193164FFDBE02EF6BE5AEC5C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226374","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226374","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226374r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226374","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000007","rule_title":"The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Back up files and directories\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52111","V-26474","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4740","uuid":"24d42c97-8f6f-402e-ae8d-30fb1d9b3e19","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 31F3C181FE05408602827A0FC3E5049E4852F65C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226375","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226375","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226375r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226375","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000011","rule_title":"The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a pagefile\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53063","V-26478","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4392","uuid":"7908dc1c-87fc-410c-bed9-3e28df70d72c","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C7F06968571672F7C09969FCEE69CACB91BAC401\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226376","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226376","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226376r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226376","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000012","rule_title":"The Create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create a token object\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52113","V-26479","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8446","uuid":"6f2db458-e246-44d4-912b-bb418193a96d","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226377","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226377","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226377r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226377","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000013","rule_title":"The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create global objects\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52114","V-26480","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2225","uuid":"2bc9db2e-68db-40a4-9cb0-26c8a837af96","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F0E1DEBA56B7E0F88DECA6C4B25BE7DCE7C4C419\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226378","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226378","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226378r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226378","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000014","rule_title":"The Create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create permanent shared objects\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53059","V-26481","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9695","uuid":"2f1001ca-a602-4e39-9de5-de78fbeb10e7","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-226379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226379","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226379","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226379r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226379","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000015","rule_title":"The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Create symbolic links\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right.  If this needs to be added manually, enter it as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right (this may be displayed as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\").  This is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could potentially expose the system to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53054","V-26482","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1895","uuid":"efb3e966-2d82-4ba7-af83-4aecff33d1ff","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DEDB34D1800B512C18DC20E7AAB9E5B9F5CEB6B5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226380","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226380","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226380r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226380","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000016","rule_title":"The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Debug programs\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Debug programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components.  This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52115","V-18010","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9981","uuid":"6ea72de3-5665-425f-9879-0b7ec0c7b907","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A79AC142C719D0E624E46183B60DC5238A7C77CF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'The Debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226381","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226381","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226381r794626_rule","rule_id":"SV-226381","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000017-DC","rule_title":"The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" to include the following:\n\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.  \n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51144","V-1155","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8088","uuid":"ddf62a95-91cf-4753-9ad9-4b8b4c38fe2c","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7FEC4CBBD4562D7BE0CBC0139D78C3196B46DEBF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226382","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226382","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226382r794627_rule","rule_id":"SV-226382","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000018-DC","rule_title":"The Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on as a batch job\" to include the following:\n\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.  \n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26483","SV-51145","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2113","uuid":"b327b270-4749-4c96-aa11-944a05062bb3","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3789EFAF16ACE83778CB4021F0999299EFCD3AC1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226383","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226383","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226383r794628_rule","rule_id":"SV-226383","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000019-DC","rule_title":"The Deny log on as a service user right must be configured to include no accounts or groups (blank) on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on as a service\" to include no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied log on as a service.  \n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-26484","SV-51146","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1019","uuid":"055bf881-bcf9-424b-8c94-ef204574765a","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3077ECD34528A9A4E1279BA64E37E290714F0CB5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on as a service user right must be configured to include no accounts or groups (blank) on domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226384","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226384","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226384","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226384r794629_rule","rule_id":"SV-226384","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000020-DC","rule_title":"The Deny log on locally user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on locally\" to include the following:\n\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.  \n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51147","V-26485","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"3373","uuid":"006a3d69-d3d1-490d-a56c-9c2b397ad02d","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C32939A9555ECCEEBD38D6254C1EF02393CDA64A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on locally user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226385","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226385","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-226385r794630_rule","rule_id":"SV-226385","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000021-DC","rule_title":"The Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" to include the following:\n\nGuests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nGuests Group","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51148","V-26486","CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1617","uuid":"a647e5e1-af28-44b9-96fa-c37b152b267d","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7465C6B28D0CA65E745435CF4E2CE4A2C8676C1B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226386","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226386","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226386","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226386r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226386","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000022-DC","rule_title":"Unauthorized accounts must not have the Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment -> \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy -> Computer Configuration -> Windows Settings -> Security Settings -> Local Policies -> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed.  This could potentially allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-51149","V-26487","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9456","uuid":"3993a721-dfbd-4e44-8407-44a506b02936","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5516777829365DF4DA1336B904556496C40139A0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Unauthorized accounts must not have the Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right on domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226387","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226387","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226387","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226387r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226387","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000023","rule_title":"The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system, which could result in a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53050","V-26488","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3734","uuid":"dcbb2725-f371-4f73-91f8-bf1989d60996","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 29CC77235718B96980EF55766E70C26D27856E33\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226388","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226388","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226388","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226388r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226388","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000024","rule_title":"The Generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Generate security audits\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Generate security audits\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Generate security audits\" user right specifies users and processes that can generate Security Log audit records, which must only be the system service accounts defined.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52116","V-26489","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8442","uuid":"54c51658-0036-4eb1-aca8-b654ca14e127","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A9DBFA5B3EE447D9C66EB263A6640569CFD69A44\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226389","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226389","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226389","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226389r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226389","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000025","rule_title":"The Impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\nService\nLocal Service\nNetwork Service\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf.  An attacker could potentially use this to elevate privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52117","V-26490","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9148","uuid":"21673ae2-b01c-4881-af1b-909e3418102a","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3AFBE5BFE84818DC3695B4BAF969860B7FD6A279\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226390","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226390","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226390","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226390r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226390","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000027","rule_title":"The Increase scheduling priority user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Increase scheduling priority\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right can change a scheduling priority causing performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52118","V-26492","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4987","uuid":"93d9aec5-a65b-4270-9b07-3ad93817745b","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":