":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53043","V-26493","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6984","uuid":"a941ccc7-cb37-4de3-b105-9db6c0845b40","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F6E5D4EFAA755DDDB98553D2B051B1EA29323958\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226392","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226392","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226392","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-226392r877392_rule","rule_id":"SV-226392","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000029","rule_title":"The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Lock pages in memory\" to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a DoS.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-52119","V-26494","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7005","uuid":"e69489c2-4351-4a41-bd11-5494a4802b53","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2012R2DC_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 063381185EAF4F8B08083AB73BCA7912555AA608\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2012 R2 domain controller."},{"group_id_src":"V-226393","group_tree":[{"id":"V-226393","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-226393","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-226393r852172_rule","rule_id":"SV-226393","rule_version":"WN12-UR-000032","rule_title":"The Manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> \"Manage auditing and security log\" to only include the following accounts or groups:\n\nAdministrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nAdministrators\n\nIf the organization has an Auditors group, the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the ISSO.\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN12-00-000010) and required frequency of changes (WN12-00-000011).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2012-2012_R2_DC_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right can manage the security log and change auditing configurations.  This could be used to clear evidence of tampering.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-53039","V-26496","CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-000171","CCI-001914"],"reference_identifier":"3072","uuid":"7bf71c80-155b-4dad-8ee3-f20fa985e8c7","stig_uuid":"3c28ef40-d2e7-4de8-80c7-a2d09a1263eb","status":"o